VALUES ('d83d2539-7f45-4014-89a7-63b4c6c4efae', 'The student wants to contrast Methods X and Y, highlight their shared objective, and frame the comparison as a defense of X''s earlier timeline. Which choice best accomplishes this goal?', '• Method X was developed in comparative poetics a decade before Method Y.
• Method X and Method Y share the objective of reducing measurement bias.
• Method Y is faster but assumes conditions X does not require.
• A 2021 review found X more robust under sparse data.
• Both methods were first applied to archival samples.
• Critics initially dismissed X as impractical.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":"Both X and Y aim to reduce measurement bias, though they differ in their assumptions. Because Y is faster, the comparison shows Y to be the superior successor in every respect.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Goal Under-Specification] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"B","text":"Both X and Y aim to reduce measurement bias, though they differ in their assumptions. Because critics dismissed X, the comparison establishes that X was ultimately impractical, as the argument is staged.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Goal Under-Specification] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."},{"id":"C","text":"Both X and Y aim to reduce measurement bias, though they differ in their assumptions. Because X preceded Y and proves more robust under sparse data, the comparison can be framed as a defense of X''s earlier timeline.","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: its second sentence is the only one that satisfies the discriminating condition."},{"id":"D","text":"Method Y is faster than X and was applied to archival samples. Both were first applied to archival samples, which settles the question of priority, on the evidence presented, within the limits set out.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[True-But-Irrelevant] Grounded in passage language but fails on a specific qualifier in its second sentence."}]'::jsonb, 'C', 'Logical Reconstruction:
Step 1: Goal parts: (1) contrast X/Y, (2) shared objective, (3) frame as defense of X''s timeline.
Step 2: Locate notes satisfying all three; ignore accurate-but-irrelevant notes.
Step 3: Reject choices that satisfy only (1)–(2) or substitute a different attribute.
Step 4: Only the choice framing the comparison as a timeline defense satisfies part (3).

Key Explanation: Choice C is the only option whose second sentence survives the discriminating step above; the others are grounded in real passage language but fail a specific qualifier.

Distractor Analysis:
- Choice A [Goal Under-Specification]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence imports a relationship the passage withholds — exactly the habit this trap exploits.
- Choice B [Goal Under-Specification]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence satisfies only part of the stated condition — exactly the habit this trap exploits.
- Choice D [True-But-Irrelevant]: a 720–740 student is drawn to its accurate first sentence, but its second sentence extends beyond the passage''s qualifiers — exactly the habit this trap exploits.

Difficulty Justification: This item is Challenge-tier because of three-to-four-part rhetorical goal whose most embedded requirement is satisfiable only by the correct subset of notes.

Score Prediction: A student scoring 750+ on DSAT R&W should answer this item correctly with deliberate reasoning; a student scoring 720–740 should find it genuinely difficult even after a careful first pass.', NULL, 'Expression of Ideas', 'Rhetorical Synthesis', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'SYN', NULL, 'hard', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"dsat_blueprint_v1":true,"tier":"challenge","challenge_tier":true,"challenged_problem":true,"difficulty_tier":"challenge","explanation_v2":true,"generator":"generate-challenge-bank.mjs","rw_subtype":"notes_synthesis","rw_format":"bullet_notes","challenge_key":"RS"}'::jsonb, true, now(), now());
