VALUES ('64422727-cb1e-4181-ba1b-3a0787d69d64', 'Which choice completes the text so that it conforms to the conventions of Standard English?', 'The monograph''s central term—teleonomy, a coinage its author, a notoriously precise stylist, defended at length—anchors the argument ______ that the later commentators, working from an abridged edition, persistently misread.', 'passage', '[{"id":"A","text":", a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Comma Splice] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"B","text":"; a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Run-on] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"C","text":" a claim","is_correct":false,"explanation":"[Restrictive/Non-Restrictive] A surface-plausible mark that either splices independent clauses or mislocates the appositive boundary."},{"id":"D","text":": a claim","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: the boundary correctly attaches the non-restrictive appositive without splicing the clause."}]'::jsonb, 'D', 'Logical Reconstruction:
